'''Michael Sheard''' ([[June 18]], [[1930s|1938]]&ndash;[[August 31]], [[2005]]) was a [[Wikipedia:Scotland|Scottish]] actor who played [[Admiral]] [[Kendal Ozzel]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. He died from cancer on August 31, 2005.

Sheard, who has portrayed Adolf Hitler five times, did so in a scene in the [[George Lucas]]&ndash;written [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade|''Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade'']], opposite another ''Star Wars'' actor, [[Harrison Ford]].

Previously, Sheard had (briefly) worked with Lucas as the U-boat captain in ''Indiana Jones and the Raiders of the Lost Ark''. In 1978, he had starred in a film version of ''Les Miserables'' alongside [[Kenneth Colley]].

He was also known to sci-fi fans for appearing numerous times in the sci-fi series [[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|''Doctor Who'']] as well as holding the record for actor playing alongside the most Doctors. The stories in which he starred include [[Wikipedia:The Ark (Doctor Who)|''The Ark'']] (1966), [[Wikipedia:The Mind of Evil|''The Mind of Evil'']] (1971), [[Wikipedia:Pyramids of Mars|''Pyramids of Mars'']] (1975), [[Wikipedia:The Invisible Enemy (Doctor Who)|''The Invisible Enemy'']] (1977), [[Wikipedia:Castrovalva|''Castrovalva'']] (1982), [[Wikipedia:Remembrance of the Daleks|''Remembrance of the Daleks'']] (1988), and [[Wikipedia:The Stones of Venice (Doctor Who audio)|''The Stones of Venice'']] (2001). He also provided the commentary for the ''Pyramids of Mars'' DVD.

In what proved to be his final appearance in front of the camera, Michael joined [[Jeremy Bulloch]], [[David Prowse]], and [[Orli Shoshan]] in the final two parts of UK fan-film trilogy ''Order of the Sith''. Michael read the opening crawl for each film. The films were made in aid of Save the Children&mdash;part of a vast range of work Michael did for charity.

He was a heavy regular on the UK science-fiction convention circuit.

